<font color="#FF0000">AGENT ORANGE EXPOSURE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jun  6 14:06:11 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
I too was exposed to agent orange.  I reported numbness in fingers, shin, buttocks and leggs in nov of 78. I was latter diagnosed to have peripheral neurophathy, by a doctor using electric testing . when I reported this to the va and requeasted a disability, it was denied because of the time fram involved, ie. peripheral  neuropathy is supposed to develope early and resolve itself quickly. I don't understand how this is possible. I encourage all vets to have an agent orange exam at your va hospital.
<p><code>-- aanderl@mugu.navy.mil  (larry  aanderud) </code><p>


